message.content: One of the most significant events that took place in Moldova in the past 5 years was the election of President Maia Sandu in November 2020. Sandu, a pro-European candidate, defeated the incumbent president Igor Dodon, marking a shift towards a more reform-oriented and Western-leaning government. Sandu's election was seen as a victory for anti-corruption efforts and a hope for greater integration with the European Union.
